      "content": "the logging approach might be too heavy for the actual production hardware, we can't really afford the overhead of a full hash map in the telemetry loop. \n\nis there a way to do this with just some basic static analysis or maybe by overriding the new/delete operators to track footprint without too much bloat? i really need to pinpoint the exact object type that's growing.",
      "source": "evaluator"
